  "text": "When extracting descriptors from photographs, we apply the Canny edge detector [CITATION_1] in a preprocess. We use a (rather large) ¼ 5 in order to suppress small lines that are unlikely to be sketched by users. We use a low threshold of 0.05 and a high threshold of 0.2 (both thresholds are taken relative to the minimum/maximum magnitude of gradient remaining after the nonmaximum suppression step).",
